ipfixMIB.name: ipfixMIB

revisions.description: Initial version, published as RFC yyyy.

ipfixMIB.contactinfo: WG charter: http://www.ietf.org/html.charters/ipfix-charter.html Mailing Lists: General Discussion: ipfix@ietf.org To Subscribe: majordomo@net.doit.wisc.edu In Body: subscribe ipfix Archive: http://ipfix.doit.wisc.edu/archive/ Editor: Atsushi Kobayashi NTT Information Sharing Platform Laboratories 3-9-11 Midori-cho Musashino-shi 180-8585 Japan Phone: +81-422-59-3978 Email: akoba@nttv6.net
ipfixMIB.description: The IPFIX collector MIB defines managed objects that are maintained by the collecting process in traffic collector or IPFIX concentrator. These objects provide informations that are exporter's profile data and received templates. Exporter's profile has that exporter's ip address and port number. In addition, these object has statistics data per session or per templates. Copyright (C) The Internet Society (2005). This version of this MIB module is part of RFC yyyy; see the RFC itself for full legal notices.

ipfixExporterTable.name: ipfixExporterTable
ipfixExporterTable.description: This table lists Exporters that received by collecting process. This process manages them.

ipfixExporterEntry.name: ipfixExporterEntry
ipfixExporterEntry.description: Defines an entry in the ipfixExporterTable

ipfixExporterIndex.name: ipfixExporterIndex
ipfixExporterIndex.description: Locally arbitrary, but unique identifier of an entry in ipfixExporterTable. The value is expected to remain constant from a re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

ipfixExporterIpAddressType.name: ipfixExporterIpAddressType
ipfixExporterIpAddressType.description: The IP address type of the exporter. The value for IPv4 is ipv4(1). The value for IPv6 is ipv6(2).

ipfixExporterIpAddress.name: ipfixExporterIpAddress
ipfixExporterIpAddress.description: The IP address of the Exporter.

ipfixLifeTimeTemplate.name: ipfixLifeTimeTemplate
ipfixLifeTimeTemplate.description: This is the time interval in seconds for the Life Time configured for the template with this session. It is only used to manage the received templates, if this protocol is UDP. The collecting process discards the template, if the templates is not refreshed within this life time.

ipfixSessionTable.name: ipfixSessionTable
ipfixSessionTable.description: This table lists sessions between exporting process and collecting process. This table has now, or has at some time in the past, established session.

ipfixSessionEntry.name: ipfixSessionEntry
ipfixSessionEntry.description: Defines an entry in the ipfixSessionTable

ipfixSessionId.name: ipfixSessionId
ipfixSessionId.description: Locally arbitrary, but unique identifier of an entry in ipfixSessionTable. The value is expected to remain constant from a re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

ipfixSessionProtocol.name: ipfixSessionProtocol
ipfixSessionProtocol.description: The transport protocol is used for receiving sampled packets from the Exporter. The recommended protocols are TCP (6), UDP (17) and SCTP (132). The default is SCTP.

ipfixSessionDstPort.name: ipfixSessionDstPort
ipfixSessionDstPort.description: The transport protocol port number of exporter which enables exporting process.

ipfixSessionSrcPort.name: ipfixSessionSrcPort
ipfixSessionSrcPort.description: The transport protocol port number of self device which enables collecting Process.

ipfixSessionStatsTable.name: ipfixSessionStatsTable
ipfixSessionStatsTable.description: This table lists sessions statistics between exporting process and collecting process. The collecting process manages them.

ipfixSessionStatsEntry.name: ipfixSessionStatsEntry
ipfixSessionStatsEntry.description: Defines an entry in the ipfixSessionStatsTable

ipfixSessionPackets.name: ipfixSessionPackets
ipfixSessionPackets.description: The number of packets received from the Exporter through this session.

ipfixSessionBytes.name: ipfixSessionBytes
ipfixSessionBytes.description: The number of bytes received from the exporter through this session.

ipfixSessionMessages.name: ipfixSessionMessages
ipfixSessionMessages.description: The number of IPFIX messages received from the exporter through this session.

ipfixSessionDiscardMessages.name: ipfixSessionDiscardMessages
ipfixSessionDiscardMessages.description: This indicates the number of received IPFIX Message that might be malformed or cant not be encoded.

ipfixSessionElapsedTime.name: ipfixSessionElapsedTime
ipfixSessionElapsedTime.description: This timer indicates how long this session has been connected. This elapsed time of the session of IPFIX presents in second.

ipfixObdomainStatsTable.name: ipfixObdomainStatsTable
ipfixObdomainStatsTable.description: This table lists statistics objects that have data per observation domain.

ipfixObdomainStatsEntry.name: ipfixObdomainStatsEntry
ipfixObdomainStatsEntry.description: Defines an entry in the ipfixObdomainStatsTable.

ipfixObdomainId.name: ipfixObdomainId
ipfixObdomainId.description: It uses the observation domain id in the received IPFIX message header.

ipfixObdomainMessages.name: ipfixObdomainMessages
ipfixObdomainMessages.description: The number of IPFIX messages received from the Exporter.

ipfixObdomainFlows.name: ipfixObdomainFlows
ipfixObdomainFlows.description: The number of flow records received from the Exporter.

ipfixObdomainTemplates.name: ipfixObdomainTemplates
ipfixObdomainTemplates.description: The number of templates received from the Exporter.

ipfixObdomainLatestSeqNumber.name: ipfixObdomainLatestSeqNumber
ipfixObdomainLatestSeqNumber.description: The latest sequence number. The collecting process overwrites to this object when it receives IPFIX message.

ipfixObdomainDisorderdSeqNumbers.name: ipfixObdomainDisorderdSeqNumbers
ipfixObdomainDisorderdSeqNumbers.description: This counter indicates inconformable numbers of sequence number. The collecting process check consistency between received sequence number and received data flows. This counter is added up this inclement, if it recognize there are some flows that have not been received.

ipfixTemplateTable.name: ipfixTemplateTable
ipfixTemplateTable.description: This table lists templates that are received by the collecting process. This process manages them.

ipfixTemplateEntry.name: ipfixTemplateEntry
ipfixTemplateEntry.description: Defines an entry in the ipfixTemplateTable

ipfixTemplateId.name: ipfixTemplateId
ipfixTemplateId.description: This number indicates the template id in the IPFIX message.

ipfixTemplateIndex.name: ipfixTemplateIndex
ipfixTemplateIndex.description: The ipfixTemplateIndex specifies the order in which the information element ids are used in the template record.

ipfixTemplateFieldId.name: ipfixTemplateFieldId
ipfixTemplateFieldId.description: This indicates the Information Element Id at position ipfixTemplateIndex in the template ipfixTemplateId. This implicitly gives the data type and state values that are received.

ipfixTemplateFieldLength.name: ipfixTemplateFieldLength
ipfixTemplateFieldLength.description: This indicates the length of each Information Element Ids. Especially, in variable length type it is specified as 65535.

ipfixTemplateStatsTable.name: ipfixTemplateStatsTable
ipfixTemplateStatsTable.description: This table lists statistics objects that have data per template.

ipfixTemplateStatsEntry.name: ipfixTemplateStatsEntry
ipfixTemplateStatsEntry.description: Defines an entry in the ipfixTemplateStatsTable

ipfixTempFlows.name: ipfixTempFlows
ipfixTempFlows.description: The number of flow records per template received from Exporter.

ipfixTempReceivedTime.name: ipfixTempReceivedTime
ipfixTempReceivedTime.description: Time that the collecting process received this template. The collecting process overwrites to this object when it receives same template.

ipfixCompliance.name: ipfixCompliance
ipfixCompliance.description: An implementation that complies to this module must implement the objects defined in the mandatory groups collectGroupExporters, collectGroupTemplates. The imeplementation of all other objects depends on the imeplementation of the corresponding functionality in the equipment.

ipfixGroupExporters.name: ipfixGroupExporters
ipfixGroupExporters.description: All objects that are basic for the management function of exporters.

ipfixGroupTemplates.name: ipfixGroupTemplates
ipfixGroupTemplates.description: All objects that are basic for the management function of templates.

ipfixGroupStatistics.name: ipfixGroupStatistics
ipfixGroupStatistics.description: All objects that are basic for the statistics function.
